Regarding antioxidant activity, the DPPH free-radical (C18H12N6O5; 2,2-diphenyl-2-picryl hydrazyl) scavenging activities were usually used as the standard assessment methods. Also, the DPPH free radical scavenging rate, as the key parameter to represent antioxidant activity, was determined via the formula:DPPH radical scavenging=1-Abssample-AbsblankAbscontrol×100.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
